  "text": "Immunohistochemistry with antibodies against transthyretin, amyloid A component, immunoglobulin and light chain antibodies can be used to type amyloid deposits. Recently, luminescent-conjugated polymer spectroscopy has been introduced as a new method to characterize amyloid deposits in histological sections [CITATION_1] .",
